Technology is changing rapidly. How a business fits into the changing landscape can be the difference between profit and loss.
<br><br>
Some of the technologies on the forefront:
<br><br>
1. AR / VR - Augmented Reality / Virtual Reality - AR and VR and very different. VR is for full immersion while AR is for Augmented immersion, like a heads-up display for a fighter pilot. With AR, static walls and resources will take on new shapes and controls to enhance the environment. Glasses and infrastructure are being developed to enable this technology.
<br><br>
2. Bots and Advanced IVR Technologies - IVR with speech enabled interfaces. Global Response is in an ideal position to take advantage of these technologies. As users decide to fail to an operator they can be continually refined to provide the best mix of service / cost / value.
<br><br>
3. IOT - The Internet of Things, Small gadgets that create a network of telemetry which can be used for alarms, monitoring, and active managment of things.
<br><br>
4. Cloud Services - Low capitol investment and unbounded scalability versus the ability to manage your own newwork and the associated uptimes.
<br><br>
5. React.js - A JavaScript framework that allows for real time web changes without page views, saving time. The alternative is Angular.
<br><br>
6. Xamerain - Mobile phone development. Let Xamaerain do the conversion into mobile development so you can stick with web technologies.
<br><br>
7. Ruby on Rails - Rapid web development environment. An elegant environment to enable the exploration of all of these technoliges.
